Based on Tabrez Mohamed's "manual" here:
https://github.com/tabrezm/r8125-synology



Driver version: 9.012.04



Prepare kernel module:

apt-get install git python3 python3-pip
git config --global http.sslverify "false"
mkdir -p /toolkit
cd /toolkit
git clone https://github.com/SynologyOpenSource/pkgscripts-ng
cd /toolkit/pkgscripts-ng
git checkout DSM7.2
./EnvDeploy -v 7.2 -p v1000                             # replace "v1000" with your platform
chroot /toolkit/build_env/ds.v1000-7.2                  # replace "v1000" with your platform
mkdir -p /usr/src
cd /usr/src
git clone https://github.com/hyllm/r8125synology
cd r8125synology/src
make



Install in Synology:

1. Copy r8215.ko to a location available from your Synology device, like a shared folder or using SCP.â€¨
2. Connect using SSH and run the following commands:
	sudo -i
	cp r8215.ko /lib/modules
	insmod /lib/modules/r8125.ko

3. Confirm the module is loaded:
	lspci -v | grep r8125
	
	Kernel driver in use: r8125

4. Set up new interface:
	ip link set up eth4                                   # replace "eth4" with your interface

At this point, you should be able to see interface details using ifconfig eth4.

5. Setup triggered task to run script "insmod /lib/modules/r8125.ko" on boot-up as root to load module at bootup.
